betterquesting:10.desc:8: There are likely many more survivors of the "experiment". I suggest we start a little colony and see if someone joins us
The builder is one of the most important buildings in your colony because it will build all the other buildings
With a quarry we can get ores faster than with traditional mining. Given that it has enough power...

We can burn ores in a normal furnace. But there is a more efficient way: The smeltery. It can smelt multiple ores at once and it even doubles them! 
 
Build it with a 2x2 bottom and place 2x2 walls on every side so that you will have a 2x2x2 volume inside. You can increase the size if you prefer it a little bigger.

To get the materials out of the smeltery we need to pour them into the casting table.

Click the faucet to pour the liquid into the table. You can also use a redstone signal to automate the process. 

To create an ingot cast you need to place any ingot in the table and pour some gold onto it.

Before we can smelt our first items, we need to find some lava to use as fuel.

Put 2 gold ingots into the smeltery and fill the tank with lava

When using the biome scanner, after you launch your satellite, do NOT hover your mouse over the remote! 
Do NOT click the remote anywhere in the world. This will cause your game to crash and/or the world to break FOREVER! 

You need to shift-click the remote after the satellite is launched and click "scan".
Shift-click the remote again and select the biome that is showing. 
While doing this, look up in the air so that you do not click on a block by accident!

After this you can use the remote as normal. If you screw up, you might need to restore a world backup. Keep the remote in your inventory bar when launching because if you can not hover over it, you will not be able to move it from a chest or your inventory. In that case, your only method do get it our of your inventory is to die!!!

The quarry needs power to operate.
 
We should build an engine and connect it to the quarry. Stirling engines burn solid fuel or lava buckets. (You will get the bucket back)

We can use a combustion engine to burn liquid fuels like oil, diesel and gasoline. 

Oil can be found in the overworld in form of oil springs. They consist of multiple hundreds buckets of oil. 

A combustion engine needs to be cooled with water after a few minutes of running or it will heat up.

The laser table can be used to create pipe pulsars and, much more important, redstone chipsets.

We can use many lasers on a single laser table to speed up the process. They can be placed above or next to the table.
The warehouse is the central storage room for your colony. You want to build it together with the deliveryman so that he moves items around in your colony to where they are needed
No Description
No Description
No Description

We should focus on a better storage system. 
All the chests make me always forget where I have put my hammer...
To enable this path we need to have a Laser and an Assembly Table

If we find an ore deposit we can build an excavator to collect it.

It is a very heavy machine and uses 4000 RF/tick to run

Now that we have a little colony we can trade with the other citizens.

You can buy and sell products for redstone
No Description

When we want to extract liquid from a tank we can use a wooden fluid pipe and a redstone engine. 

But there is a better way to do it: A pipe pulsar can be directly placed onto a pipe. It takes up less space and looks nice.

The Redstone Chipset is an important part of engineering. 
We will need it to build large machines.
I have found a few scientists who have agreed to work on a research project to investigate rocket science. But the research is expensive and we will need a lot of materials...

We will need to build some dedicated machines to produce more advanced materials. Craft a Rolling machine and a Lathe.

Shift click the Holo Projector to select the machine you want to build and click it anywhere on the ground. 

Use shift + mouse wheel to project different layers of the structure

That looks like volcanic ash. 

We should investigate its origin with the help of the warp controller

ffThere was this experiment... A new source of energy they said... But it went very wrong! They turned our home land - the earth's moon - into a dust dessert without any atmosphere. You barely made it out alive and crash landed on the planet earth. Your starship was destroyed and evaporated into the air. But you are determined to survive and make our moon habitable again!

With the research done we can now ask the scientists to build a rocket assembling machine for us.

We just need to provide the materials.
And pay them of course!

The machine needs to be placed diagonally next to a launch pad.

betterquesting:10.name:8: I know a guy who knows a guy
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
I have heard of someone who is very skilled at working with steam. He offers to build steam engines for locomotives. In return for payment, of course...

This could come in handy when we need to transport ore from the excavators to our processing facility.
Now that we have the necessary resources, we can start working on rocket science.

We can double our ores in a smeltery. But we can 3x them with the industrial crusher!

Look at the manual for more information!
No Description
The Engineer's Manual contains the knowledge of heavy engineering. We should create one!
Fund a large scale research program to investigate advanced rocket science.

The simple stirling and combustion engines are not compatible with the complex engineering machines. 

We need to create an energy bridge to transfer energy into machines until we have more advanced power generators.

Place the three blocks next to each other. You can pipe energy into the MJ consumer and extract energy with wire connectors from the FE producer.

We will soon need it to create materials that are too complex to be made in a crafting table.

Let's build this workbench!

Find more details in the Engineer's Manual.

We can use wires and connectors to transfer RF/FE energy.

There are different types of wires and connectors for low, medium, and high voltage. We can use relays to connect multiple wires of the same type together.

HV connectors can handle 8000 RF/tick
MV connectors can handle 1000 RF/tick
LV connectors can handle 256 RF/tick

Wires can handle about 4 times what the connectors can transfer. If they have too much current they will burn.
Now that we have the necessary resources, we can start working on rocket science

Use the Coke Oven to burn coal to coal coke. 
This will give it a higher burning time and you get access to creosote oil.

Build the oven in a 3x3x3 shape and activate it with the hammer

Use the Blast Furnace to create steel. 

Build it in a 3x3x3 shape and activate it with the hammer.

We will need a projector to help us when we build the big machines. 

We can program the projector by putting it next to the Engineer's Manual in a crafting table. The projector will be programmed to display the machine that is selected in the manual.

We will need a Biome Changer Satellite to transform the moon turf back into dirt. 

It can be constructed using a satellite builder. Just use the remote controller instead of an ID chip.

The satellite must orbit the moon to be able to change its surface.

This is a very dangerous machine and if you handle the remote incorrectly it can break the universe. You'd better not mess around with it. Just scan and select the moon biome and put it into the Terraformer.

Carefully read the bug alert in order to continue your journey!
We can use a Core Sample Drill to scan for ores and fluids deep below the surface. I recommend to have a capacitor with you to power the drill.

The Improved Blast Furnace uses reinforced bricks and can create steel much faster.

The process can be further accelerated by blowing in some extra air.

Look at the manual for more information.

You found an oil reservoir? Great! Now we can build a pumpjack to pump it up.

Lets get all the materials together to build a pumpjack!

Capacitors are an easy way to store energy. 
They come in different sizes: lv, mv and hv.

We can use the hammer to change a side to input / output energy. Hold shift to change the opposite side.

Blue is usually input while orange is usually output.

Capacitory can be charged with the power of redstone. This is a good alternative to use if you do not want to craft an energy bridge.

Hover your mouse over a capacitor and press U.
It will show some crafting recipes. Combining a capacitor with redstone will fully charge it.

Oil by itself is very useless. While a combustion engine can burn it, the energy output can not even sustain a pumpjack. We need to refine it. 

Build a Distillation Tower to convert oil to diesel and gasoline!
If you find oil in the overworld, you can bucket it up or use a pump to pump it up. But it will be depleted fast so you might want to look for underground oil reservoirs.

This is a really big furnace. It can smelt many ores into ingots very quickly and can also produce a lot of steel.

Look at the manual for more information.
Get a bucket of diesel!
Get a bucket of Gasoline!

I have heard that you can refine biodiesel from plants but it is less energy dense and we would need a full plantation to "grow" fuel. 

You might want to check it out but I say we focus on normal diesel for now.

The diesel generator is a great energy source to power heavy machines. 

It produces 4000 RF/tick, that is 1333 Rf/tick per output connector.

It is the perfect choice for getting started with your energy network!

A Steam Turbing is very fuel efficient. It needs a boiler to heat water to steam. The steam can be piped into the turbine. We can recycle some of the water from the turbing exhaust.

To maximize your steam production use distilled water for your boiler. It will produce more steam resulting in more energy produced.

Energy output: ~12000 RF/tick

The Gas Turbine burns gasoline or rocket fuel to produce ~12000 RF/tick.

It takes up less space than the steam turbine and requires much less materials. 
And it can start up fast. 
It also does not require any water to run.

The downside is that it uses a little bit more fuel and it needs a starting help. Check the Manual for more information.

The Portable Generator produced about 250 RF/tick and runs on gasoline.

It can also burn rocket fuel at 500 RF/tick.
You are now able to generate a huge amount of energy. Great work!

Looks like that starship was traveling close to a gas giant. 

With the help of the Artifact we can locate Gas Giants

The Improved Blast Furnace uses reinforced bricks and can create steel much faster.

The process can be further accelerated by blowing in some extra air.

Look at the manual for more information.
Such a big machine only to press coke to HOP dust... Or can it do something else too?
No Description
No Description
No Description

We can also reverse the process and transform FE/RF energy into MJ.

This can be useful to run a high speed quarry or power many lasers at once with heavy power generation methods.

The Controller is the heart of a storage network. It needs energy to operate. The amount of energy needed depends on the size of the network.

Every other part of our network needs to be connected to the controller by placing them next to each other.

Cables can also be used as an alternative to connect parts of your network if you do not want to place them all next to each other.

So I was working on this new storage system and I have some very interesting ideas. 

Look, I have created this blueprint. 
We can use it to build our storage network!

The Grid will show you all items in our network. 

You also need it to access items in the network.

Research into optical systems will allow us to develop complex lenses. 

We will need a ton of glass and for this project.
It is like a normal Grid. It just adds a crafting interface.

The Observatory is a large structure that is capable of peering out into the cosmos and pinpoint distant asteroid or abandoned starships that may contain valuable materials. It's primary function is to locate these distant objects and program their coordinates into asteroid chips.

In order for the Observatory to function, the structure must have at least one data bus with at least 100 distance data. 

We can ask the scientists to assist us in building this machine.

For the item storage I had a very unique idea:
We will store them on disks!

So the first thing to do is to craft a disk drive.

The Interface can be used to extract items from our network or to put items into our network.

Items can be put in with a hopper or a conveyor belt. 

Items can be taken out with a hopper or a conveyor belt too. Just tell the interface what items you want it to provide. To remove items from the list: shift click

Now we need to craft the disks to store the items. I say we start with a small one. You can scale up later of course.

Put the disk into the disk drive!

Scientists have found a way to assemble functioning rockets. However, it is a long way between building rockets and terraforming a moon. 

Further research will be necessary.

We will need more data to continue our research. The scientists suggest to launch satellites for data collection. We can build them in a Satellite Builder.

The Satellite Builder needs to be placed on top of a power input plug.

This little antenna can transfer data from one data bus to another. 

Two of them need to be linked together with the Linker tool. One of them needs to be in extract mode and don't forget to turn them on when using!

We need a launch pad to assemble rockets. Build it in a 3x3 form and place the tower next to it. 

The tower bottom needs to touch one of the launch pad blocks from the side.

A rocket needs fuel. We can build a simple electrolyzer or the massive crucible battery to split water into H2 and O2. 

The electrolyzer is cheap to build but needs a lot of power and is slow. The battery is fast and efficient but it is more expensive to build. You decide.

The two gases can be combined later in a chemical reactor to produce fuel.

betterquesting:10.name:8: completing research in basic rocket science
betterquesting:10.desc:8: No Description

The Fueling Station will transfer the rocket fuel into the rocket. 

It needs to be linked to the Rocket Assembly Machine with a Linker tool

Now that we did all the preparations we can start to build our first rocket.

It needs to have:

Engines
Fuel Tanks
A Guidance Computer
(A seat)

To launch a rocket you have two options:

A Monitoring Station linked to the Assembly Machine

A seat (and a space suit)

To set your destination you need to put a special ID chip into the Guidance Computer. 

To fly to other planets (or return to earth) you will need a Planet ID chip.

You can shift click the rocket to access the inventory. You can press V to open the inventory if you are inside the rocket.

For your first flight I recommend you to set the destination to earth so that you just fly up and come right back to the ground.

If you want to fly to the moon I recommend you take a Fueling Station, a Linker, a charged capacitor and a few buckets of rocket fuel with you or you might never return...
No Description

To build a satellite you will need the following components:

- a satellite
- a sensor
- solar panels
- data storage units


I suggest that our first satellite should be a distance scanner. 
We should use 3 large solar panels to provide it with a good amount of power. At least one data storage unit is also needed to store the collected data. 

Note: If you don't need all the storage slots, you can fit in even more solar panels!

There are abandoned spaceships and pieces of debris everywhere in space. 

We can send autonomous mining rockets to collect resources and parts that might come in useful later. 

These rockets will need to be equipped with special drilling heads to complete their mission.
We finally found a working drill system now. I lost count of how many rockets we lost in the process....

We found an Artifact! Great!

I will show you how we can locate the planet with the help of the Artifact.

Fill the Warp Controller with data and place the Artifact inside the Controller.

Now you can scan for a Planet. You can place a Planet ID Chip in the Controller that will show you what planet you have discovered

An important part of rocket science is the construction of a space station.

We should investigate possible ways to build such a station!

To terraform the atmosphere of moon we will need a lot of nitrogen and oxygen.

The only way to obtain these resources in large quantities is gas mining. 

We need to investigate methods for collecting these gases using unmanned vehicles.

The advanced rocket science research program was a great success!

The scientists found a way to modify the atmosphere and the surface of planets. But they need more material samples from different planets to put the plan in action. 

We can use the observatory to search for abandoned starships. They might be able to provide the information we need to locate planets.

That is oxidized ferric sand. 

I think it's home planet must be some kind of giant desert.

The development of a warp system will allow for long-distance travel between planets.

From the latest research it is estimated that the moon contains large amounts of Dilithium. It is a very energy-rich substance that could be used as a fuel, but further investigation is needed.

This is a strange dust.

Even the slightest friction causes it to become electrically charged - hence the glitter.
No Description

On your space station, build:

- A Warp Core (use the Holo Projector)

- A Warp Controller

Now that we have the Warp System set up we can fill the Warp Core with Dilithium Crystals. 

You can select the planet you want to travel to in the warp controller. Be sure to have the Artifact in the Controller too or the Warp will fail.

We can put multiple artifacts in the controller so that we don't always have to swap them.

In the case of a warp failure, it may be necessary to reinsert the dilithium crystals.

Unlike the Rocket Assembling Machine, the Unmanned Vehicle Assembler builds the craft horizontally instead of vertically.

Once the Unmanned Vehicle Assembler is placed, Structure Tower blocks can be placed on the top and sides of the machine to determine the area in which to build the vehicle.


A bar must extend from the top of the vertical tower to determine the length of the area to build.
The Terraformer will need oxygen and nitrogen gas to generate an atmosphere.

The Terraformer is a very large machine. It consists mainly of many advanced machine structures and a good chunk of concrete.

We can order the heart of the machine from the scientists.

All the work and research has paid off.

Now we have the all the technology and materials to make our moon habitable again!

It will probably be years before the original climate is restored, but the foundations can now be set.

Congratulations!

betterquesting:10.desc:8:
We found an Artifact! Great!

I will show you how we can locate the planet with the help of the Artifact.

On your space station, build:

- A Warp Core (use the Holo Projector)

- A Warp Controller

Fill the Controller with data and place the Artifact inside the Controller.

Now you can scan for a Planet. You can place a Planet ID Chip in the Controller that will show you what planet you have discovered

The Warp Core is the most important part of a Warp Drive.

We can now order them from the Scientists.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Research into basic rocket science completed
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Now that we have a basic understanding of Rocket Science we should focus on out main goal: terraforming Moon.

We will need a larger team of scientists for this.

Get some readstone ready!
Now that we have the heart of the machine we can finally build the Terraformer!

The Crystallizer is a multi-block construction which allows for creation of dilithium crystals and silicon boule.

Items are inserted via the input hatch and the goods can be retrieved from the output hatch. Use the Holo-Projector to complete the structure, then right click the Crystallizer machine block.

The Cutting Machine's primary purpose is to cut silicon boules into silicon wafers and circuit plates into basic circuits. By default you get four circuits per plate, making them a relatively cheap but high-processing material. Use the Holo-Projector to complete the structure, then right click the Cutting machine block.

Additionally, it can cut logs into 6 planks instead of crafting them into 4. Use higher tier Coils and Motors to increase performance.

Once the satellite is in orbit we can extract it's data using a Satellite Terminal.

Put the Satellite ID chip into the terminal. On Connection it will output collected data into the terminal.

Data can be taken out of the terminal with data storage units or wireless transceivers.

To get your satellite into orbit you have to launch it with a rocket. 

Equip your rocket with a Satellite Bay. 

A Guidance Computer with a planet ID chip targeting earth is recommended - or the rocket will never come back!

A tank is recommended for storing large quantities of liquids.

A valve in the lower layers can output liquids.

A valve in the upper layers can be used to input liquids.

A valve at the lowest level outputs liquids automatically into a connected pipe.

A valve can not be placed at the edges of the tank.

Once we find a silt deposit we can crush the gravel to sand and smelt it in a furnace to glass. 

We can use the assembler to craft bottles and the mixer to brew potions. 

At the end we fill it into bottles with a bottling machine.

The quarry has left huge holes in the ground. 

We can use the space to store large amounts of oil and pump it up again if needed.

Or you just fill them up with water.

It takes so much time to always bucket the oil into a crafting table. 

Can this be automated with an assembler?

I have a plan about how we can connect our satellite terminals together and transfer all the data into a central storage. 

What do you think? Should we try it?

It is very boring to always unload the gas from rockets and send them back to work by hand.

We should try to automate this process...

We should use these trains to get the ores out of our excavators.

I can think of a small railway network with automatic loaders and unloaders...

With the help of docking pads we can program our rockets to fly to specific locations, load and unload, fuel up and more!

If you are ready - let's go!
No Description
No Description

To transfer MJ energy we can use energy pipes. 

A wooden energy pipe can connect to energy producers.

A stone energy pipe can connect to other pipes and energy consumers.

The simple fluid pipes can only handle a limited amount of mb/s.

Iron pipes can transfer liquids much faster!

At night time the observatory can scan the sky for asteroids. 

It will consume 100 distance data to perform a scan.
We can scan as long as there is enough data available until we find something of interest.

The observatory can program Asteroid ID chips.

To transfer fluids we can use simple fluid pipes.

A wooden pipe is an extraction pipe. It needs to be powerd by a redstone engine or a pipe pulsar.

So far we have build a distance scanner. 

However, there are 2 other types of data collection satellites.

We will construct a Mass Scanner next. I made a list of the materials needed.

Remeber, you can add up to 5 solar panels it you want to.

The last type of data we need is called Composition data.

We need a composition scanner to collect it.

Well, now we have a problem...

We managed to build a warp drive, but we have no idea where to go!

To locate a planet, we need to find an artifact from it. 

There are some abandoned spaceships drifting around near the earth from time to time. Maybe they can help us.

We should use the observatory and scan for them!
No Description

0:10.command:8: say The warp drive is of no use if we don't know the positions of other planets. Find more information in the quest book!

betterquesting:10.desc:8: No Description

To use a rocket for space mining it needs to be equipped with drills. 

more drills = faster mining

A chest is also needed to store the collected materials.
Make sure that the chest is not blocked from opening!

A guidance computer with a programmed Asteroid ID chip will get the rocket to it's destination and back to earth.

An Asteroid ID chip that has been programmed in the observatory needs to be filled with data.

We can do this in an Astrobody Data Processor.
This machine takes data from it's data inputs and writes it to the chip. 

I recommend you use a wireless transceiver to automate the data transfer from the satellite terminals to the data processor.

I will make a list of the required materials.
Use the Holo-Projector to build the machine!

Lack of data can lead to poor mining results.

Be sure to connect the data inputs to the correct data type!!! For example, you cannot input distance data in the mass data slot.

The machine needs about 2K RF/second and it takes about 16 minutes to fill the data to 100%

I made a list of all the materials needed to build the observatory.

We need 3 good lenses and an enhanced motor to be able to look deep into space.

Lower quality materials will not be able to detect rare objects!

The observatory needs energy to program a chip and it needs a clear night sky to operate. It can not operate in rainy weather.

Because there is no oxygen in space, you need to construct a space suit.

Due to the difficult nature of working with a modular spacesuit, a Suit Workstation must be used to install, remove, and modify components built into the modular spacesuit.

The Suit Workstation does not require any power or tools to operate.

The space suit can be crafted using a normal crafting table.

You can add modules to it using the Suit Workstation.

For example, to fly to the moon or into space, you must be fully clothed and your spacesuit must have an oxygen-filled pressurized tank integrated into it.

You can upgrade your tanks to better ones to store more oxygen.

To fill your space suit with oxygen you can simple stand on top of a Gas Charge Pad.

It does not need energy. It only needs to be supplied with the gas you want to charge your space suit with.

The Space Station Assembler can be ordered from the scientists in the same way as the Rocket Assembling Machine. 

However, rather than build rockets, it builds space station modules from the blocks placed on the pad.

To build a new station, a Satellite Bay must be placed in the top left slot and an unprogrammed station chip must be placed in the top right slot.

Also your structure must be build on the launch pad.

Once these goals are met, a space station can be built. 

To build your station, click "scan" in the assembler and if there are no errors you can click "build".

You will now get a space station item and a programmed Space Station ID chip.

You will send your station to space the same way you do it with satellites.

You can use a Guidance Computer to bring the rocket back to earth after the station has been launched.

You can also add a seat to the rocket and put your station ID chip into the guidance computer. This will take you up to your station.

I recommend you make a chip copy in the satellite builder and store it somewhere safe. I you lose the chip you will not be able to go to your station again.
